radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is retrocecal very dilated with multiple appendicoliths. There is hazy increased density and stranding in surrounding fat as well as a small amount of free fluid in the right pelvis. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are within normal limits. No retroperitoneal, mesenteric, pelvic, or inguinal lymphadenopathy. No abdominal aortic aneurysm or worrisome osseous lesions.
